about.summary: Create data summaries for quality control, extensive reports for exploring data, as well as publication-ready univariate or bivariate tables in several formats (plain text, HTML,LaTeX, PDF, Word or Excel. Create figures to quickly visualise the distribution of your data (boxplots, barplots, normality-plots, etc.). Display statistics (mean, median, frequencies, incidences, etc.). Perform the appropriate tests (t-test, Analysis of variance, Kruskal-Wallis, Fisher, log-rank, ...) depending on the nature of the described variable (normal, non-normal or qualitative). Summarize genetic data (Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms) data displaying Allele Frequencies and performing Hardy-Weinberg Equilibrium tests among other typical statistics and tests for these kind of data.

name: r-comparegroups
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '4.4.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-comparegroups
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/compareGroups_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/compareGroups/compareGroups_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e150dfb86ebe65fa8d0b33a2b495055f11e53c2ccea28fe87ba4ceb11ca6d8df

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-hardyweinberg
    - r-snpassoc
    - r-chron
    - r-flextable
    - r-kableextra
    - r-knitr
    - r-officer
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-survival
    - r-writexl
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-hardyweinberg
    - r-snpassoc
    - r-chron
    - r-flextable
    - r-kableextra
    - r-knitr
    - r-officer
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-survival
    - r-writexl

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('compareGroups')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('compareGroups')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: www.comparegroups.eu
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  summary: Create data summaries for quality control, extensive reports for exploring data, as
    well as publication-ready univariate or bivariate tables in several formats (plain
    text, HTML,LaTeX, PDF, Word or Excel. Create figures to quickly visualise the distribution
    of your data (boxplots, barplots, normality-plots, etc.). Display statistics (mean,
    median, frequencies, incidences, etc.). Perform the appropriate tests (t-test, Analysis
    of variance, Kruskal-Wallis, Fisher, log-rank, ...) depending on the nature of the
    described variable (normal, non-normal or qualitative). Summarize genetic data (Single
    Nucleotide Polymorphisms) data displaying Allele Frequencies and performing Hardy-Weinberg
    Equilibrium tests among other typical statistics and tests for these kind of data.
  license_family: GPL
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
